# Emails

CSA Admin uses two types of emails to communicate with your members:

- [**Automatic emails**](/mail_templates): sent automatically during specific events (new invoice, renewal, activity reminder, ...). You can customize their content and activate/deactivate them.
- [**Newsletters**](/newsletters): group emails that you compose and send manually (or schedule) to all or part of your members.

Both types use the same template language and formatting options described below.

## Liquid Template Language {#liquid}

Email templates use the [Liquid](https://shopify.github.io/liquid) template language, which lets you insert dynamic member-specific data and add conditional logic. Despite a "group" sending, the content of each email is generated individually based on the information of each member (name, language, membership, ...).

### Displaying Data

Use double curly braces to insert a value:

~~~ liquid
<p>Hello {{ member.name }},</p>
<p>Your next delivery is on {{ basket.delivery.date }}.</p>
~~~

### Conditions

Use `{% if %}` to show content only when a condition is met:

~~~ liquid
{% if basket.contents.size > 0 %}
  <h2>Basket Contents</h2>
  ...
{% endif %}
~~~

You can use `and`, `or`, as well as `{% elsif %}` and `{% else %}` to combine conditions:

~~~ liquid
{% if membership.trial_baskets_count > 0 %}
  <p>You are still in your trial period ({{ membership.trial_baskets_count }} baskets remaining).</p>
{% elsif membership.activity_participations_missing_count > 0 %}
  <p>You still have {{ membership.activity_participations_missing_count }} activity(s) to complete.</p>
{% else %}
  <p>Everything is up to date, thank you!</p>
{% endif %}
~~~

### Loops

Use `{% for %}` to repeat content for each item in a list:

~~~ liquid
<ul>
  {% for content in basket.contents %}
    <li>{{ content.product }} ({{ content.quantity }})</li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
~~~

## Formatting Tags {#formatting-tags}

In addition to standard HTML, several special formatting tags are available:

**Highlight block** — Displays content in a colored highlight box, useful for important announcements:

~~~ liquid
{% highlight %}
  <p><strong>📣 Important!</strong></p>
  <p>Your basket will be extra large this week.</p>
{% endhighlight %}
~~~

**Lowlight block** — Displays content in a subtle grey box, useful for secondary information:

~~~ liquid
{% lowlight %}
  <p>Manage your registrations from
    <a href="{{ member.activities_url }}">your account</a>.</p>
{% endlowlight %}
~~~

**Button** — Displays a prominent call-to-action button. Pass the name of a variable containing the URL:

~~~ liquid
{% button member.activities_url %}
  Sign up for an activity
{% endbutton %}
~~~

## Data Preview {#data-preview}

When editing an email template or a newsletter template, a preview panel is displayed below the code editor. This preview shows your template rendered with sample data for each language.

Below each preview, a data panel shows the exact data structure available to your template. This data is generated semi-randomly from your actual organization data. You can modify the values in this panel to test how your template renders with different scenarios (e.g. empty basket contents, zero missing activities, etc.).

> The data preview is the best way to discover all available variables and test your template. Each type of email template has its own set of available data — always check the preview panel to see what's available.
